{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2ed6341f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Loop and domain calling\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to identify chromatin loops and TADs from the seqFISH+ dataset from [Takei et al, 2021](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-020-03126-2). The 25Kb subset used here can be downloaded from the [4DN data portal](https://data.4dnucleome.org) with file IDs: 4DNFIHF3JCBY (biological replicate 1) and 4DNFIQXONUUH (biological replicate 2)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "00f61b72",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import arcfish as af"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d9a5016e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading FOF_CT-core file\n",
    "\n",
    "`arcfish.pp.FOF_CT_Loader` is the base class to read in FOF_CT files. The input can be a string, a list, or a dictionary like here. It can also read in other FOF_CT files other than FOF_CT-core (check api documentation [here](../api/generated/arcfish.pp.FOF_CT_Loader.rst)).\n",
    "\n",
    "For FOF_CT-core files, `loader.chr_ids` show a list of available chromosomes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "c14e01ea",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array(['chr1', 'chr2', 'chr3', 'chr4', 'chr5', 'chr6', 'chr7', 'chr8',\n",
       "       'chr9', 'chr10', 'chr11', 'chr12', 'chr13', 'chr14', 'chr15',\n",
       "       'chr16', 'chr17', 'chr18', 'chr19', 'chrX'], dtype=object)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "loader = af.pp.FOF_CT_Loader({\n",
    "    \"rep1\": \"4DNFIHF3JCBY.csv\", \"rep2\": \"4DNFIQXONUUH.csv\"\n",
    "}, nm_ratio={c: 1000 for c in \"XYZ\"})\n",
    "loader.chr_ids"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5698a1f3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `create_adata` function creates an AnnData object for a specific chromosome with the following fields:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. `n_obs`: the number of chromatin traces\n",
    "2. `n_vars`: the number of imaging loci\n",
    "3. `X`, `Y`, and `Z`: 3D coordinates\n",
    "4. `Chrom_Start` and `Chrom_End`: 1D genomic location of each locus\n",
    "5. `Chrom`: chromosome number (\"chr6\" in this case)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "734c395b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "AnnData object with n_obs × n_vars = 921 × 60\n",
       "    var: 'Chrom_Start', 'Chrom_End'\n",
       "    uns: 'Chrom'\n",
       "    layers: 'X', 'Y', 'Z'"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "adata = loader.create_adata(\"chr6\")\n",
    "adata"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ea7f6034",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can calculate the median pairwise distance matrix and visualize it using `af.pp.median_pdist` and `af.pl.pairwise_heatmap`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "de4dfa45",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "AnnData object with n_obs × n_vars = 921 × 60\n",
       "    var: 'Chrom_Start', 'Chrom_End'\n",
       "    uns: 'Chrom'\n",
       "    layers: 'X', 'Y', 'Z'\n",
       "    varp: 'med_dist'"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "af.pp.median_pdist(adata, inplace=True)\n",
    "adata"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "b97d01bc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x300 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(4, 3))\n",
    "af.pl.pairwise_heatmap(adata.varp[\"med_dist\"], ax=ax, cmap=\"RdBu\",\n",
    "                       title=\"Median Pairwise Distance Matrix (chr6)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "972bc23b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loop calling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0328752c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First we filter and normalize the data. This appends 'med_dist', 'raw_var_X', 'raw_var_Y', 'raw_var_Z', 'count_X', 'count_Y', 'count_Z', 'var_X', 'var_Y', 'var_Z' to the anndata object, where var_* are the axis variance matrices."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "3414babf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "AnnData object with n_obs × n_vars = 921 × 60\n",
       "    var: 'Chrom_Start', 'Chrom_End'\n",
       "    uns: 'Chrom'\n",
       "    layers: 'X', 'Y', 'Z'\n",
       "    varp: 'med_dist', 'raw_var_X', 'raw_var_Y', 'raw_var_Z', 'count_X', 'count_Y', 'count_Z', 'var_X', 'var_Y', 'var_Z'"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "af.pp.filter_normalize(adata)\n",
    "adata"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "489cd4ef",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Create a `LoopCaller` object with an FDR cutoff of 0.1. The `call_loops()` method returns a dictionary containing the analysis results."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "14e1e245",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "dict_keys(['axis_stat', 'axis_pval', 'stat', 'pval', 'fdr', 'candidate', 'label', 'summit', 'final'])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "caller = af.tl.LoopCaller(fdr_cutoff=0.1)\n",
    "loop_result = caller.call_loops(adata)\n",
    "loop_result.keys()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1bfb608b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we create four heatmaps to visualize the loop calling process: the original distance matrix, FDR values, loop candidates grouped by clusters, and the final loop calls."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "a7b72ab4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x200 with 8 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(9, 2))\n",
    "af.pl.pairwise_heatmap(adata.varp[\"med_dist\"], ax=axes[0], cmap=\"RdBu\",\n",
    "                       title=\"Pairwise Distance\")\n",
    "af.pl.pairwise_heatmap(loop_result[\"fdr\"], ax=axes[1], cmap=\"Greys_r\",\n",
    "                       title=\"Loop FDR\")\n",
    "af.pl.pairwise_heatmap(loop_result[\"label\"], ax=axes[2], cmap=\"tab20c\",\n",
    "                       title=\"Loop candidates\\n(colored by cluster)\")\n",
    "af.pl.pairwise_heatmap(loop_result[\"final\"], ax=axes[3], cmap=\"Reds\",\n",
    "                       title=\"Final loops\")"
   ]
  },
  {

   "metadata": {},

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "45d09f3b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   ]
  },
